Log in to the AWS Management Console and open Route 53.

Go to Hosted Zones and select your domain (e.g., example.com).

Click Create record.

Record name: Enter your subdomain (e.g., dev or blog).

Record type: Select A - Routes traffic to an IPv4 address.

Value: Paste your EC2 Elastic IP address.

Click Create records.

Create sub domain folders using Putty

mkdir /var/www/poker/

	sudo chown -R ubuntu:mygrp /var/www/poker/
	sudo chmod -R g+rwx /var/www/poker/
	sudo systemctl restart apache2

Create Config files

cd /etc/apache2/sites-available/

ls

sudo nano sub.example.com.conf

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName beta.test-all-in-statistics.pro
    DocumentRoot /var/www/beta

    <Directory /var/www/beta>
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    # Fixes React Router 404 on refresh
    FallbackResource /index.html

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/one_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/one_access.log combined

	RewriteEngine on
	RewriteCond %{SERVER_NAME} =beta.test-all-in-statistics.pro
	RewriteRule ^ https://%{SERVER_NAME}%{REQUEST_URI} [END,NE,R=permanent]

</VirtualHost>

OR USE THIS 

<VirtualHost *:80>

    ServerName mps.test-all-in-statistics.pro
    DocumentRoot /var/www/mps

    <Directory /var/www/mps>
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    RewriteEngine On

    # Serve real files/directories normally
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # React fallback
    FallbackResource /index.html

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/mps_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/mps_access.log combined

</VirtualHost>

sudo a2ensite sub.example.com.conf
sudo systemctl restart apache2

Activate subdomains here

sudo certbot --apache
or solo
sudo certbot --apache -d sub.example.com
